<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN284-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – tumpai; tuṟai – pāṭāṇpāṭṭu. ōrampōkiyar.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN284">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>varukatil vallē varukatil valleṉa</l>
<l>vēntuviṭu viḻutū tāṅkāṅ kicaippa</l>
<l>nūlari mālai cūṭik kāliṟ</l>
<l>ṟamiyaṉ vanta mūti lāḷa</l>
<l>ṉaruñcaman tāṅki muṉṉiṉ ṟeṟinta</l>
<l>vorukai yirumpiṇat teyiṟumiṟai yākat</l>
<l>tirinta vāyvā ṭiruttāt</l>
<l>taṉakkirin tāṉaip peyarpuṟa nakumē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>“Please come quickly, please come quickly”,</l>
<l>when everywhere the excellent message sent by the king sounded,</l>
<l>the man from a ancient house, come alone</l>
<l>on foot, wearing a garland of several threads,</l>
<l>corrected [his] sword with crookedly twisted blade</l>
<l>on the tusk of the large corpse with a trunk</l>
<l>whom he had thrown down, standing in front [of it], enduring difficult battle,</l>
<l>[and] laughed at the moving back of the one who retreated from him.  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
